@notice Extremely simple linear interest rate model: rate = base + slope * utilization
 - Utilization in 1e18 (e.g., 0.45e18 => 45%)
 - Returns borrow rate per second in 1e18 (e.g., 0.05e18/year => ~1.58e-9 per second)

@title RateGovernor
 @notice Minimal timelocked governance helper for scheduling interest-rate model updates.
 @dev The governor queues arbitrary calls to interest rate models (or any ownable contract)
      and executes them after a configurable delay. Designed to own the interest rate
      strategies so research-driven parameter adjustments can be rolled out safely.

@title DynamicInterestRateModel
@notice An interest rate model that adjusts its base rate based on a global repo rate.
The borrow rate is a combination of a base rate (influenced by the global repo rate)
and a variable rate based on utilization.
r(u) = (base * globalRepoRate) + slope * u

@notice Calculates the current borrow rate per second.
@param utilization The current utilization of the asset pool (totalBorrows / (totalCash + totalBorrows)).
@return The borrow rate per second, scaled by 1e18.

@notice Updates the parameters of the interest rate model.
@param _baseRateMultiplier The new multiplier for the global repo rate.
@param _slopeAPR The new slope for the utilization curve.

@notice Adaptive utilization-sensitive rate model inspired by Fraxlend's time-weighted design.
 @dev The model keeps a mutable APR state that nudges upward when utilization stays above the
      target band, downward when below, and reverts toward a neutral APR when healthy.

